What does the following java function perform ? (Assume int occupies four bytes of storage)
<pre>
Public static int f(int a) {
  //Pre-conditions : a>0 and no overflow/underflow occurs
  int b = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
    b = b << 1;
    b = b | (a & 1);
    a = a >>> 1; // This is a logical shift
  }
  Return b;
}
</pre>

